UBS Hires Kamat as Chairman of Asia Financials Coverage

-- B y   P h i l i p   L a g e r k r a n s e r   a n d   E l e n a   L o g u t e n k o v a
-- 
2011-05-11T11:39:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-11/ubs-appoints-aashish-kamat-as-asia-financials-coverage-chairman.html
UBS AG (UBSN) ,  Switzerland ’s biggest bank,
hired Aashish Kamat as chairman of financial institutions
coverage for the Asia-Pacific region, according to an internal
memo obtained by Bloomberg News.  Kamat will start at UBS on June 1 and report to Alex Wilmot-Sitwell and Yoon Chi-Won, co-chief executive officers of
UBS’s operations in the region, according to the document. A
spokesman for UBS confirmed the contents of the memo.  Kamat will work with all units of the investment bank in
the region to advise financial institutions on the challenges
they face in the current economic, credit and regulatory
environments, Wilmot-Sitwell and Yoon said in the memo.  Kamat, who has worked in banking for 22 years, moved to
 Asia  as chief financial officer of  JPMorgan Chase & Co. (JPM) ’s
business in the region in 2007 and later added the
responsibilities of the chief operating officer. Prior to that,
Kamat was the global controller of JPMorgan’s investment bank
and worked as CFO of Bank of America Corp.’s investment bank for
four years, according to the memo.  To contact the reporter on this story:
